## Frequently Asked Questions

### What is the best metal for a men's diamond ring?

Platinum is the best metal for daily wear: hardest, most durable, no rhodium plating needed, resizable. 14k white gold is the budget alternative at 20–30% less cost. Tantalum is the choice for buyers who want a dark grey industrial aesthetic.

### How wide should a men's wedding band be?

5–6mm for classic proportions. 7–8mm for a statement. 9mm+ for fashion-forward. Diamond band widths on Blue Nile are primarily 6–7.5mm, which is the standard range.

### Can a diamond men's ring be resized?

Most can — platinum and gold bands without full-eternity diamond setting can be resized by a jeweller. Full eternity bands (diamonds all the way around) cannot be resized. Tantalum and tungsten cannot be resized.

### How much diamond is in a men's pavé edge ring?

The Diagonal Lined Pavé Edge rings have 1/8 ct tw (approximately 0.125 carats) of melee diamonds. These are very small accent stones — the visual effect is a subtle sparkle at the band edge, not a statement diamond. The [Men's Pavé Edge 1/6 ct ($2,180)](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/mens-diamond-pave-edge-wedding-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-6-ct-tw-item-196242?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) has slightly more coverage.

### Is the tantalum ring safe?

Yes — unlike tungsten, tantalum can be cut off in a medical emergency. Tantalum is biocompatible and hypoallergenic. The only functional limitation is that it cannot be resized.

### What is the black diamond ring option?

The [Men's Black Diamond Pavé Edge Black Rhodium Platinum at $1,526](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/mens-black-diamond-pave-edge-wedding-ring-with-black-rhodium-in-platinum-1-6-ct-tw-item-196249?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) uses black diamonds (natural diamonds with graphite inclusions creating black colour) set in platinum coated with black rhodium. The all-black aesthetic is dramatic and masculine. Black diamonds are natural stones but are not graded by GIA on the standard colour-clarity scale.

